stylometry: An advantage of simulation models is that it imitates real life solutions and incorparates uncertainity in put variables by getting random and various values. it shows an entire distribution of results, not just a single result, with different values for the uncertain quantities, which is analyzed as different scenarios. In business it is useful to see how your system is sensitive to change in operating conditions. It answers what-if questions without actually having to make a physical example. An example is a car company planning on making a new car and entering it into the marke. They would want to try to simulate the profit based on ordering costs, producing the model, car demand, and other factors to get a idea of what their profits could be.
